1 B. It shall be unlawful for any person to knowingly smoke
2 tobacco or marijuana or use a vapor product in a motor vehicle while
3 in the presence of a minor. Any person in violation of the
4 provisions of this section shall be assessed a fine not less than
5 Fifty Dollars ($50.00) nor more than One Hundred Dollars ($100.00)
6 which shall be deposited into the Tobacco Prevention and Cessation
7 Revolving Fund established pursuant to Section 1-105d of Title 63 of
8 the Oklahoma Statutes.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
